ğŸ§ª Test locally:
Create dummy files named like flags:

bash
Copy
Edit
touch -- '--some-flag=payload'
Then run the command with * to see if your file triggers misbehavior:

bash
Copy
Edit
tar -cf test.tar.gz *
ğŸ§  CPTS/Exam Takeaways
Donâ€™t just think: â€œOh, itâ€™s a tar cron job.â€

Think: â€œIs * used? Can I inject flags via filenames? Can any of those flags lead to command execution?â€

If you find a job or script that matches that pattern â€” drop --checkpoint-action bombs and wait for root.

